Alembic migrations — Polymnia backend
=====================================

Schema source of truth: api/models.py (SQLModel). Alembic owns the *evolution* of
the live schema; SQLModel.create_all is dev/POC only (see api/session.py).

Config
------
- Connection: derived from DATABASE_URL by env.py (via api.session), normalised to
  the psycopg 3 driver. There is no sqlalchemy.url in alembic.ini on purpose.
- target_metadata = SQLModel.metadata, so `--autogenerate` diffs against the models.
- Run all commands from backend/ with uv, e.g. `uv run alembic ...`.

Common commands
---------------
- Apply latest:            uv run alembic upgrade head
- Roll back one:           uv run alembic downgrade -1
- New migration (auto):    uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
- Show current revision:   uv run alembic current
- History:                 uv run alembic history

Workflow when the model changes
-------------------------------
1. Edit api/models.py.
2. `uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "..."`.
3. Review the generated file (autogenerate misses some ALTERs — check it).
4. `uv run alembic upgrade head`, then re-run autogenerate to confirm an empty diff.

Dev bootstrap without migrations
--------------------------------
Set POLYMNIA_DEV_CREATE_ALL=1 to let the app build the schema via create_all at
startup (fast local iteration). Prod never sets it: schema is applied with
`uv run alembic upgrade head` before the app boots.
